17/05/2005
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Former Romanian President Ion Iliescu will undergo a thorough medical examination following problems with blood pressure at the weekend, Bucharest media reported Monday (16 May). 
According to the reports, he has been suffering from high blood pressure. 
In April, the veteran political figure lost PSD internal elections for the party presidency to former Foreign Minister Mircea Geoana. 
(Nine o'clock - 16/05/05)
